\begin{eqnarray} && b_d = \left( \frac{(1-s_d^e)(1-\gamma)\psi_d \chi_d^e}{(1-s_d^i)\chi_d^i} \right)^{(1-\gamma)/\gamma}\\ && b_n = \left( \frac{(1-s_n^e)(1-\gamma)\psi_n \chi_n^e}{(1-s_n^i)\chi_n^i} \right)^{(1-\gamma)/\gamma}\\ && (\rho + z_d)(1-s_d^e) \chi_d^e \psi_d = \frac{L_d(\lambda_d-1)}{1-\alpha}-(1-s_d^i)\chi_d^ib_d^{1/1-\gamma}\\ && (\rho + z_n)(1-s_n^e) \chi_n^e \psi_n = \frac{L_n(\lambda_n-1)}{1-\theta}-(1-s_n^i)\chi_n^ib_n^{1/1-\gamma} \\ && L_n+L_d+ RD = 1 \\ && rK=w\left(\frac{\theta}{1-\theta}L_n+\frac{\alpha}{1-\alpha}L_d \right) \\ && P_d = \frac{\lambda_d r^\alpha w^{1-\alpha}}{A} \\ && 1 = \frac{\lambda_n r^\theta w^{1-\theta}}{\Theta} \\ && \tau_d = b_d + z_d\\ && \tau_n = b_n + z_n\\ && r = \left(\rho + \delta + \frac{\tau_d \log(\lambda_d)}{1-\alpha}\right)(1-s^x)P_d \\ && \left(\frac{\tau_d \log(\lambda_d)}{1-\alpha}+ \delta \right)K = D \\ && C = N \\ && RD = \chi_d^i b_d^{1/1-\gamma}+\chi_n^i b_n^{1/1-\gamma}+\chi_d^e\psi_d z_d + \chi_n^e\psi_n z_n\\ &&N = \left(\frac{\theta}{1-\theta}\frac{w}{r}\right)^\theta L_n\\ &&D = \left(\frac{\alpha}{1-\alpha}\frac{w}{r}\right)^\alpha L_d\\ && W = \frac{1}{\rho}\left(\log C_0 + \frac{g_C}{\rho} \right) \end{eqnarray}

import numpy as np

class innovation(object):
    def __init__(self, alpha=.33, theta=.33, delta=.05, rho=.03, gamma =.6, lambda_d=1.21390951, lambda_n=1.02788162,
                 psi_d=.18, psi_n = 0.2, chi_ed= 4.65252389, chi_en = 1.66782674, s_x =0, s_ed = 0, s_en=0, s_id=0.2, s_in=0.2,
                 Qn = 1.0, Qd=1.0, chi_id= 4.65252389, chi_in = 1.66782674, iota_n = 0, iota_d =0,x0=np.ones(16)/2):
                 self.alpha, self.theta, self.delta, self.rho, self.gamma = alpha, theta, delta, rho, gamma
                 self.lambda_d, self.lambda_n = lambda_d, lambda_n
                 self.psi_d, self.psi_n, self.chi_ed, self.chi_en = psi_d, psi_n, chi_ed, chi_en
                 self.s_x, self.s_ed, self.s_en, self.s_id, self.s_in = s_x,s_ed, s_en, s_id, s_in
                 self.Qn, self.Qd = Qn, Qd
                 self.chi_id, self.chi_in = chi_id, chi_in
                 self.iota_n, self.iota_d = iota_n, iota_d
                 self.alpham = (self.alpha**self.alpha)*(1-self.alpha)**(1-self.alpha)
                 self.thetam = (self.theta**self.theta)*(1-self.theta)**(1-self.theta)
                 self.x0 = x0
    
    def Funcs(self,x,corr_call):
        b_n, b_d, z_n, z_d, tau_n, tau_d = x[0:6]
        Ln, Ld = x[6:8]
        D, N, C, K, RD = x[8:13]
        w, r, Pd = x[13:]
        
        if corr_call:
            self.s_x = 1-1/self.lambda_d
        
        Q = self.Qn*self.Qd**((self.theta)/(1-self.alpha))
        F=np.zeros(16)
        alpham = (self.alpha**self.alpha)*(1-self.alpha)**(1-self.alpha)
        thetam = (self.theta**self.theta)*(1-self.theta)**(1-self.theta)
        gammah = 1.0/(1-self.gamma)
        An = (1.0-self.s_en)*(1-self.gamma)*self.psi_n*self.chi_en
        Bn = (1.0-self.s_in)*self.chi_in
        Ad = (1.0-self.s_ed)*(1-self.gamma)*self.psi_d*self.chi_ed
        Bd = (1.0-self.s_id)*self.chi_id
        F[0]=b_n - z_n*(An/Bn)**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma)
        F[1]=b_d - z_d*(Ad/Bd)**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma)
        F[2]=((self.rho+z_d)*(1.0-self.s_ed)*self.chi_ed*self.psi_d*z_d**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma)) 
              - Ld*(self.lambda_d -1)/(1.0-self.alpha)+(1-self.s_id)*self.chi_id*b_d**gammah)
        F[3]=((self.rho+z_n)*(1.0-self.s_en)*self.chi_en*self.psi_n*z_n**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma))
              - Ln*(self.lambda_n -1)/(1.0-self.theta)+(1-self.s_in)*self.chi_in*b_n**gammah)
        F[4]=1-Ln-Ld-RD
        F[5]=K*r - w*(self.theta/(1-self.theta)*Ln + self.alpha/(1-self.alpha)*Ld)
        F[6]=Pd - self.lambda_d*r**self.alpha*w**(1-self.alpha)/(alpham)
        F[7]=1 - self.lambda_n*r**self.theta*w**(1-self.theta)/(thetam)
        F[8]=tau_n - b_n - z_n
        F[9]=tau_d - b_d - z_d
        F[10]=r-(self.rho+self.delta+tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha))*(1-self.s_x)*Pd
        F[11]=(tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha)+self.delta)*K-D
        F[12]=C-N
        F[13]=(RD-self.chi_id*b_d**gammah-self.chi_in*b_n**gammah-self.chi_ed*self.psi_d*z_d**gammah
               -self.chi_en*self.psi_n*z_n**gammah)
        F[14]=N-(self.theta/(1-self.theta)*w/r)**self.theta*Ln
        F[15]=D-(self.alpha/(1-self.alpha)*w/r)**self.alpha*Ld
        return F

   
    
    def equilibrium(self,correct_call=False):
        x0=self.x0
        sol= scipy.optimize.root(self.Funcs, x0, correct_call, method = 'hybr')
        x0 = sol.x
        self.b_n=sol.x[0]
        self.b_d=sol.x[1]
        self.z_n=sol.x[2]
        self.z_d=sol.x[3]
        self.tau_n=sol.x[4]
        self.tau_d=sol.x[5]
        self.g_c = self.theta/(1-self.alpha)*self.tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)+self.tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
        self.g_r = self.tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n) - (1-self.theta)/(1-self.alpha)*self.tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)
        self.C = sol.x[10]
        self.Ln = sol.x[6]
        self.Ld = sol.x[7]
        self.D  = sol.x[8]
        self.K  = sol.x[11]
        self.RD = sol.x[12]
        self.w  = sol.x[13]
        self.r  = sol.x[14]
        self.R  = self.g_c+self.rho
        self.p_d= sol.x[15]
        self.Kn = (self.theta/(1-self.theta))*self.Ln*self.w/self.r
        self.Kd = (self.alpha/(1-self.alpha))*self.Ld*self.w/self.r
        self.value_n = ((self.w*(self.lambda_n-1)*self.Ln/(1-self.theta)-self.w*(1-self.s_in)*self.chi_in*self.b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma)))
                       /(self.rho+self.z_n))
        self.value_d = ((self.w*(self.lambda_d-1)*self.Ld/(1-self.alpha)-self.w*(1-self.s_id)*self.chi_id*self.b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))
                       /(self.rho+self.z_d))

        self.T = (self.s_en*self.psi_n*self.chi_en*self.z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                  self.s_ed*self.psi_d*self.chi_ed*self.z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                  self.s_in*self.chi_in*self.b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                  self.s_id*self.chi_id*self.b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))*self.w+self.s_x*self.p_d*self.D

        #return np.array([self.b_n, self.b_d, self.z_n, self.z_d, self.g_c, self.g_r]) 
        self.init_C = self.C
        self.init_tau_n = self.tau_n
        self.init_tau_d = self.tau_d
        self.init_g_C = self.g_c
        self.init_k   = self.K
        return  np.array([self.g_c, self.init_g_C,self.tau_n, self.tau_d,self.z_n, self.b_n, self.z_d, 
                 self.b_d, self.Ln, self.Ld, self.Kn, self.Kd, self.K]) 


#         return  ('CE = ', 1, 'TE = ', 1, 'optimal growth = ', self.g_c.round(decimals=2), 
#                  'decentral growth = ', self.init_g_C.round(decimals=2), 'tau_n = ', self.tau_n.round(decimals=2),
#                 'tau_d = ', self.tau_d.round(decimals=2),'z_n = ', self.z_n.round(decimals=2), 
#                  'b_n = ', self.b_n.round(decimals=2), 'z_d = ', self.z_d.round(decimals=2), 
#                  'b_d = ', self.b_d.round(decimals=2),'Ln = ', self.Ln.round(decimals=2),
#                  'Ld = ', self.Ld.round(decimals=2), 'Kn = ', self.Kn.round(decimals=2),
#                  'Kd = ', self.Kd.round(decimals=2), 'K = ', self.K.round(decimals=2)) 
    
    def distance(self,x,targets,corr_call,alt_calib):
        if alt_calib:
            self.psi_n = self.psi_d = x[0]
            self.lambda_n = self.lambda_d = x[1]
            self.chi_ed=self.chi_id=self.chi_en=self.chi_in=x[2]
        else:
            self.psi_n = x[0]
            self.psi_d = x[1]
            self.lambda_n = x[2]
            self.lambda_d = x[3]
            self.chi_ed=self.chi_id=x[4]
            self.chi_en=self.chi_in=x[5]
        self.equilibrium(correct_call=corr_call)
        if alt_calib:
            M = [0,0,0]
            M[0] = targets[0]-(self.b_n*self.Ln+self.b_d*self.Ld)/(self.Ln+self.Ld)
            M[1] = targets[1]-(self.z_n*self.Ln+self.z_d*self.Ld)/(self.Ln+self.Ld)
            M[2]=targets[2]-self.g_c
        else:    
            M=[0,0,0,0,0,0]
            M[0]=targets[0]-self.b_n
            M[1]=targets[1]-self.b_d
            M[2]=targets[2]-self.z_d
            M[3]=targets[3]-self.z_n
            M[4]=targets[4]-self.g_c
            M[5]=targets[5]-self.g_r
        
        return M
    
    def inn_distance(self,x):
        self.s_in, self.s_id = x
        self.s_en, self.s_ed = max(0,(self.s_in-self.gamma)/(1-self.gamma)),max(0,(self.s_id-self.gamma)/(1-self.gamma))  
        self.equilibrium()
        M = np.array([self.tau_n,self.tau_d])-self.optimum_inn    
        return M
    
    def calibration(self,targets,corr_call=False,alt_calib=False):
        if alt_calib:
            x0= [.2, 1.12, 2]
        else:
            x0= [.2, .2, 1.12, 1.24, 2,2]
        if corr_call:
            self.s_en = (self.s_in-self.gamma)/(1-self.gamma)
            self.s_ed = (self.s_id-self.gamma)/(1-self.gamma)
        args = targets, corr_call,alt_calib
        return scipy.optimize.leastsq(self.distance, x0,args)
    
    
    
    def optimum_subsidy(self):
        x0= [.8,.8]
        n = 100
        gammas = np.linspace(.4,.8,n)

        s_optimum = np.zeros((2,n))
        self.s_x = 1-1/self.lambda_d
        
        for index,gamma in enumerate(gammas):
            self.gamma = gamma
            self.planner_ss()
            sol=scipy.optimize.leastsq(self.inn_distance,x0)
            s_optimum[:,index]=sol[0]
            
        %matplotlib inline
        plt.plot(gammas,s_optimum[0,:],'r',linewidth=2,label='Consumption')
        plt.plot(gammas,s_optimum[1,:],'b',linewidth=2,label='Investment')
        plt.xlabel(r'$\gamma $',fontsize=18)
        plt.ylabel('R&D Subsidy')
        plt.legend(loc='best')
        plt.title('Optimal R&D Subsidy')
        plt.savefig('./com-stats/gamma.pdf')
    
    def planner_eq(self, x):
        
        K_n   = x[0]
        K_d   = x[1]
        L_n   = x[2]
        L_d   = x[3]
        tau_n = x[4]
        tau_d = x[5]
        S = [0,0,0,0,0,0]
            
        psi_nbar = (self.psi_n+self.psi_n**(1/self.gamma))/(1+self.psi_n**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma))**(1/(1-self.gamma))
        psi_dbar = (self.psi_d+self.psi_d**(1/self.gamma))/(1+self.psi_d**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma))**(1/(1-self.gamma))
    

        S[0] = (np.log(self.lambda_n)*L_n - self.rho*(1-self.theta)/(1-self.gamma)*
                self.chi_en*psi_nbar*tau_n**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma)))
        S[1] = (np.log(self.lambda_d)*L_d - self.rho*(1-self.alpha)/(1-self.gamma)*
                self.chi_ed*psi_dbar*tau_d**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma)))
        S[2] = (-self.delta + self.alpha*K_d**(self.alpha-1)*L_d**(1-self.alpha) - self.rho 
                - tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha))
        S[3] = (1-self.alpha)/self.alpha*K_d/L_d - (1-self.theta)/self.theta*K_n/L_n
        S[4] = 1 - L_n - L_d - self.chi_en*psi_nbar*tau_n**(1/(1-self.gamma)) - self.chi_ed*psi_dbar*tau_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))
        S[5] = K_d**self.alpha*L_d**(1-self.alpha)/(K_n+K_d)-self.delta - tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha)

        return S
 
    def planner_ss(self):
        x0= [self.Kn,self.Kd,self.Ln,self.Ld,self.tau_n,self.tau_d]
        sol= scipy.optimize.root(self.planner_eq, x0)

        K_n   = sol.x[0]
        K_d   = sol.x[1]
        L_n   = sol.x[2]
        L_d   = sol.x[3]
        tau_n = sol.x[4]
        tau_d = sol.x[5]

        self.sp_eq = np.array([K_n,K_d,L_n,L_d,tau_n,tau_d])
        self.optimum_inn=[tau_n,tau_d]
        z_n   = tau_n/(1+self.psi_n**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma))
        b_n   = tau_n - z_n
        z_d   = tau_d/(1+self.psi_d**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma))
        b_d   = tau_d - z_d

        self.ss_Co = K_n**self.theta*L_n**(1-self.theta)*self.Qn
        g_C = self.theta/(1-self.alpha)*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)+tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
        CE = (self.ss_Co/self.init_C)*np.exp((-self.init_g_C+g_C)/self.rho)
        TE = (self.init_C/self.ss_Co)*np.exp((self.init_g_C-g_C)/self.rho)
        self.K_planner = K_n+K_d
        return np.array([CE, TE, g_C,self.init_g_C, tau_n,tau_d,z_n, b_n, z_d, b_d,
               L_n, L_d, K_n, K_d, K_n+K_d]) 


#         return ('CE = ', CE, 'TE = ', TE, 'optimal growth = ', g_C, 'decentral growth = ', self.init_g_C, 
#                 'tau_n = ', tau_n, 'tau_d = ', tau_d, 'z_n = ', z_n, 'b_n = ', b_n, 'z_d = ', z_d, 'b_d = ', b_d,
#                'Ln = ', L_n, 'Ld = ', L_d, 'Kn = ', K_n, 'Kd = ', K_d, 'K = ', K_n+K_d) 
    
    def planner_cs(self,alpha):
        self.alpha = alpha
        return self.planner_ss()
    
    def competitive_cs(self,alpha):
        self.alpha = alpha
        return self.equilibrium()

    def controls_ss(self,x0,y0):
        K,xibar, psibar,sigmabar,Qn,Qd = y0
        C,Kn,Kd,Ln,Ld,tau_n,tau_d = x0
        
        psi_nbar = (self.psi_n+self.psi_n**(1/self.gamma))/(1+self.psi_n**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma))**(1/(1-self.gamma))
        psi_dbar = (self.psi_d+self.psi_d**(1/self.gamma))/(1+self.psi_d**((1-self.gamma)/self.gamma))**(1/(1-self.gamma))

        F = np.zeros(7)
        F[0]=Ln*xibar*(1-self.alpha)*Kd**self.alpha*Ld**(-self.alpha)-(1-self.theta)
        F[1]=Ln*psibar*np.log(self.lambda_n)-1/(1-self.gamma)*self.chi_en*psi_nbar*tau_n**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma))*(1-self.theta)
        F[2]=Ln*sigmabar*np.log(self.lambda_d)-1/(1-self.gamma)*self.chi_ed*psi_dbar*tau_d**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma))*(1-self.theta)       
        F[3]=Kn*xibar*self.alpha*Kd**(self.alpha-1)*Ld**(1-self.alpha)-self.theta
        F[4]=1 - Ln - Ld - self.chi_en*psi_nbar*tau_n**(1/(1-self.gamma)) - self.chi_ed*psi_dbar*tau_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))
        F[5]=K-Kn-Kd
        F[6]=C-Kn**self.theta*Ln**(1-self.theta)
        
        return F
    
    def differentials_ss(self,y,t):
        Kn,Kd,Ln,Ld,taun,taud = self.sp_eq
        C  = Kn**self.theta*Ln**(1-self.theta)
        #x0=(C,Kn,Kd,Ln,Ld,taun,taud)
        x0 = np.ones(7)/3
        sol= scipy.optimize.root(self.controls_ss, x0,y, method = 'hybr')
        C,Kn,Kd,Ln,Ld,tau_n,tau_d = sol.x
        K,xibar, psibar,sigmabar,Qn,Qd = y
        
        kdot     = Kd**self.alpha*Ld**(1-self.alpha)-K*(self.delta+tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha))
        xidot    = (self.rho+self.delta+tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha))*xibar-self.theta/Kn
        psidot   = self.rho*psibar-1
        sigmadot = self.rho*sigmabar-xibar*Kd**self.alpha*Ld**(1-self.alpha)
        Qndot    = Qn*tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
        Qddot    = Qd*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)
        
        dydt     = [-kdot,-xidot,-psidot,-sigmadot,-Qndot,-Qddot]
        
        return dydt
    
    def transition_ss(self,years,days,outyears,graph=False):
        self.planner_ss()
        Kn,Kd,Ln,Ld,taun,taud = self.sp_eq
        K_ss     = Kn+Kd
        psi_ss   = 1/self.rho
        xi_ss    = (1-self.theta)/Ln/((1-self.alpha)*Kd**self.alpha*Ld**(-self.alpha))
        sigma_ss = xi_ss*Kd**self.alpha*Ld**(1-self.alpha)/self.rho
        Qn_ss    = 1
        Qd_ss    = 1
        C  = Kn**self.theta*Ln**(1-self.theta)
        X  = Kd**self.alpha*Ld**(1-self.alpha)
        
        
        self.equilibrium()
        Kinit = self.init_k
        init_c = self.C
        Cinit = np.ones(years*days)*self.C
        Xinit = np.ones(years*days)*self.D
        taun_init, taud_init = self.tau_n, self.tau_d      
        self.Kinit = np.ones(years*days)*Kinit
        
        org_g_C = taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)+taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha)
        g_C     = taun*np.log(self.lambda_n)+taud*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha) 
        
        # start the integration process by disturbing capital
        Qn = 1.0
        Qd = 1.0

        if ( K_ss-.00002 <= Kinit <= K_ss+.00002):
            return (C/init_c)*np.exp((-org_g_C+g_C)/self.rho)
        elif (K_ss < Kinit):
            y0 = np.array([K_ss,xi_ss,psi_ss,sigma_ss,Qn_ss,Qd_ss])+np.array([0.0002,0,0,0,0,0])
        else:
            y0 = np.array([K_ss,xi_ss,psi_ss,sigma_ss,Qn_ss,Qd_ss])+np.array([-.0002,0,0,0,0,0])
            
        t = np.linspace(0, years, years*days)
        m = np.zeros(years*days)
        sol = odeint(self.differentials_ss, y0, t)
        self.trans = sol
        
        transitions = np.zeros((7,years*days))
        for i in range(years*days):
            Kn,Kd,Ln,Ld,taun,taud = self.sp_eq
            C  = Kn**self.theta*Ln**(1-self.theta)
            x0=(C,Kn,Kd,Ln,Ld,taun,taud)
            sol= scipy.optimize.root(self.controls_ss, x0,self.trans[i,:], method = 'hybr')
            transitions[:,i]=sol.x
            
        
        if graph:
            %matplotlib inline
            plt.plot(t, self.trans[:, 0], 'red', linewidth=2,label='capital')
            plt.plot(t, transitions[0, :], 'k', linewidth=2,label='consumption')
            plt.plot(t, self.trans[:, 4], 'g',linewidth=2, label='Qn')
            plt.plot(t, self.trans[:, 5], 'c',linewidth=2, label='Qd')
            plt.plot(t,self.Kinit, 'c--', linewidth=2, label='Initial K')
            plt.legend(loc='best')
            plt.xlabel('time')
            plt.title('Transition (Reverse)')
            plt.show()

        for i in range(years*days):
            if (K_ss < Kinit):
                m[i] = -1 if self.trans[i,0] > self.Kinit[i] else 0
            else:
                m[i] = -1 if self.trans[i,0] < self.Kinit[i] else 0

        t0 = np.argmax(m<0)
        Ktrans     = self.trans[0:t0,0]
        Ctrans     = transitions[0,0:t0]
        Xtrans     = transitions[2,0:t0]**self.alpha*transitions[4,0:t0]**(1-self.alpha)
        taun_trans = transitions[5,0:t0]
        taud_trans = transitions[6,0:t0]
        Qntrans    = self.trans[0:t0,4]
        Qdtrans    = self.trans[0:t0,5]

        Kseq = np.concatenate((self.Kinit[0:outyears*days],Ktrans[::-1],np.ones(outyears*days)*K_ss))
        Cseq = np.concatenate((Cinit[0:outyears*days],Ctrans[::-1],np.ones(outyears*days)*C))
        Xseq = np.concatenate((Xinit[0:outyears*days],Xtrans[::-1],np.ones(outyears*days)*X))

        taunseq = np.concatenate((taun_init*np.ones(outyears*days),taun_trans[::-1],taun*np.ones(outyears*days)))
        taudseq = np.concatenate((taud_init*np.ones(outyears*days),taud_trans[::-1],taud*np.ones(outyears*days)))
        
        Qn_earlier = [1/np.exp(taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)*i/days) for i in range(outyears*days)]
        Qd_earlier = [1/np.exp(taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)*i/days) for i in range(outyears*days)]
        
        Qntrans    = self.trans[0:t0,4]/self.trans[t0-1,4]*np.exp(taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)/days)
        Qdtrans    = self.trans[0:t0,5]/self.trans[t0-1,5]*np.exp(taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)/days)
        
        Qn_later  = [Qntrans[0]*np.exp(taun*np.log(self.lambda_n)*i/days) for i in range(outyears*days)]
        Qd_later  = [Qdtrans[0]*np.exp(taud*np.log(self.lambda_d)*i/days) for i in range(outyears*days)]
        
        self.Qnseq = np.concatenate((Qn_earlier[::-1],Qntrans[::-1],Qn_later))
        self.Qdseq = np.concatenate((Qd_earlier[::-1],Qdtrans[::-1],Qd_later))

        
        self.Cseq = Cseq
        self.taunseq = taunseq
        self.taudseq = taudseq
        self.Conseq = Cseq*self.Qnseq*self.Qdseq**(self.theta/(1-self.alpha))
        self.Invseq = Xseq*self.Qdseq**(1/(1-self.alpha))
        
        time = len(self.Conseq)
        
        self.Kseq = Kseq
        self.Capseq = Kseq*self.Qdseq**(1/(1-self.alpha))
        
        self.utility = [np.exp(-self.rho*(i-outyears*days)/days)*np.log(self.Conseq[i]) for i in range(time)]
        
        self.Conseqalt = np.zeros(time)
        self.Conseqalt[0:outyears*days] = self.Conseq[0:outyears*days]
        
        self.Invseqalt = np.zeros(time)
        self.Invseqalt[0:outyears*days] = self.Invseq[0:outyears*days]
        
        self.Pdseq     = [np.exp((taunseq[i]*np.log(self.lambda_n)-taudseq[i]*np.log(self.lambda_d))*i/days) for i in range(time)]
        self.Pdseq     = self.Pdseq/self.Pdseq[outyears*days-1]
        
        self.GDP       = self.Conseq+self.Pdseq*self.Invseq
    
        
        for i in range(outyears*days,time):
            self.Conseqalt[i]=self.Conseqalt[i-1]*np.exp((taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)+
                                                        taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha))/days)
            self.Invseqalt[i]=self.Invseqalt[i-1]*np.exp((taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha))/days)
        
        self.utilityalt=[np.exp(-self.rho*(i-outyears*days)/days)*np.log(self.Conseqalt[i]) for i in range(time)]
        

        self.Conseq_cg = np.zeros(time)
        self.Conseq_cg[0:outyears*days+1] = self.Conseq[0:outyears*days+1]
        

        

        #for i in range(outyears*days+1,time):
        #    self.Conseq_cg[i]=self.Conseq_cg[i-1]*np.exp((taun*np.log(self.lambda_n)+
        #                                                taud*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha))/days)

        #self.con_growth = np.zeros(time)
        #self.con_growth[0:outyears*days]=org_g_C
        #self.con_growth[outyears*days+t0:]=g_C

        org_C    = self.Conseqalt[outyears*days]
        org_C_ss = self.Conseqalt[outyears*days+t0]
        C0       = self.Conseq[outyears*days]
        Css      = self.Conseq[outyears*days+t0]
 
        CE = (Css/org_C_ss)*np.exp((-org_g_C+g_C)/self.rho)
        
        welfare_new = (np.exp(-self.rho*t0/days)*(np.log(Css)+g_C/self.rho)/self.rho
                       +trapz(self.utility[outyears*days:outyears*days+t0],dx=1/days))
        
        CE_alt = np.exp(welfare_new*self.rho-org_g_C/self.rho-np.log(org_C))

        return CE_alt, CE

    


        
    def controls(self,x0,y0):
        C, K, Vn, Vd,Qn,Qd = y0
        w,r,R,D, Ln, Ld,tau_n,tau_d,b_n,b_d,z_n,z_d,T,Pd = x0
        F = np.zeros(14)
        F[0] = C-(self.theta/(1-self.theta)*w/r)**self.theta*Ln
        F[1] = D-(self.alpha/(1-self.alpha)*w/r)**self.alpha*Ld
        F[2] = self.thetam-self.lambda_n*r**self.theta*w**(1-self.theta)
        F[3] = Pd*self.alpham-self.lambda_d*r**self.alpha*w**(1-self.alpha)
        F[4] = r*K-w*(self.theta*Ln/(1-self.theta)+self.alpha*Ld/(1-self.alpha))
        F[5] = (1-Ln-Ld-self.chi_id*b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))-self.chi_in*b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))
               -self.psi_d*self.chi_ed*z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))-self.psi_n*self.chi_en*z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma)))
        F[6] = Vn-w*(1-self.s_in)*self.chi_in*b_n**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma))/(1-self.gamma)
        F[7] = Vd-w*(1-self.s_id)*self.chi_id*b_d**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma))/(1-self.gamma)
        F[8] = Vn-w*(1-self.s_en)*self.psi_n*self.chi_en*z_n**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma))
        F[9] = Vd-w*(1-self.s_ed)*self.psi_d*self.chi_ed*z_d**(self.gamma/(1-self.gamma))
        F[10]= tau_n-z_n-b_n
        F[11]= tau_d-z_d-b_d
        F[12]= T-w*(self.s_id*self.chi_id*b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))+self.s_in*self.chi_in*b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))
               +self.s_ed*self.psi_d*self.chi_ed*z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))
                    +self.s_en*self.psi_n*self.chi_en*z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma)))-self.s_x*Pd*D
        F[13]= Pd*(R+self.delta-tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
                   +(1-self.theta)/(1-self.alpha)*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d))-r/(1-self.s_x)
        
        return F
  
    def differentials(self,y,t):
        x0 = [self.w,self.r,self.R,self.D,self.Ln,self.Ld,self.tau_n,self.tau_d,
             self.b_n,self.b_d,self.z_n,self.z_d,self.T,self.p_d]
        #x0 = np.ones(14)
        sol= scipy.optimize.root(self.controls, x0,y, method = 'hybr')
        w,r,R,D, Ln, Ld,tau_n,tau_d,b_n,b_d,z_n,z_d,T,Pd = sol.x
        [self.w,self.r,self.R,self.D,self.Ln,self.Ld,self.tau_n,self.tau_d,
             self.b_n,self.b_d,self.z_n,self.z_d,self.T,self.p_d]=sol.x
        C, K, Vn, Vd,Qn,Qd = y
        cdot = C*(R-self.rho-tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
                  -self.theta/(1-self.alpha)*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d))
        kdot = D - K*(self.delta+tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)/(1-self.alpha))
        #adot = w*(Ln+Ld)+r*K+R*A-Pd*D-C-T-A*(tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
        #                                     +self.theta/(1-self.alpha)*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d))
        Vndot = (Vn*(R-tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
                  -self.theta/(1-self.alpha)*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)+z_n)
                -w*Ln*(self.lambda_n-1)/(1-self.theta)+w*(1-self.s_in)*self.chi_in*b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma)))
        Vddot = (Vd*(R-tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
                  -self.theta/(1-self.alpha)*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)+z_d)
                -w*Ld*(self.lambda_d-1)/(1-self.alpha)+w*(1-self.s_id)*self.chi_id*b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))
        Qndot = Qn*tau_n*np.log(self.lambda_n)
        Qddot = Qd*tau_d*np.log(self.lambda_d)
        dydt = [-cdot,-kdot,-Vndot,-Vddot,-Qndot,-Qddot]
        return dydt
    
    def technology(self,y,t):
        Qn, Qd = y
        Qndot = Qn*self.tnseq[self.period]*np.log(self.lambda_n)
        Qddot = Qd*self.tdseq[self.period]*np.log(self.lambda_d)
        
        self.period += self.period
        dydt = [Qndot,Qddot]
        
        return dydt

    def transition(self,init_subs,subs,years,days,outyears,graph=False):
        
        
        # call equilibrium function to get the initial steady state values
        self.s_x,self.s_in,self.s_id,self.s_en,self.s_ed=init_subs
        self.equilibrium()
        Kinit = self.init_k
        #print ('Kinit',Kinit)
        init_c = self.C
        Cinit = np.ones(years*days)*self.C
        taun_init, taud_init = self.tau_n, self.tau_d      
        self.Kinit = np.ones(years*days)*Kinit
        # set the subsidies
        self.s_x,self.s_in,self.s_id,self.s_en,self.s_ed=subs
        
        # call the equilibrium again to get the new steady state values
        self.equilibrium()
        taun_late = self.tau_n
        taud_late = self.tau_d
        C, K, Vn, Vd = self.C,self.K,self.value_n,self.value_d
        #print ('K late',K)
        org_g_C = taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)+taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha)
        g_C     = taun_late*np.log(self.lambda_n)+taud_late*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha) 
        # start the integration process by disturbing capital
        # i'm still not sure whether this is the correct approach
        Qn = 1.0
        Qd = 1.0
        
        if ( K-.00002 <= Kinit <= K+.00002):
            return ((C/init_c)*np.exp((-org_g_C+g_C)/self.rho),1,1,1)
        elif (K < Kinit):
            y0 = np.array([C,K,Vn,Vd,Qn,Qd])+np.array([0.0002,+.00002,+0.00002,+0.00067,0,0])
            #y0 = np.array([C,K,Vn,Vd,Qn,Qd])+np.array([0,+.00002,0,0,0,0])
        else:
            y0 = np.array([C,K,Vn,Vd,Qn,Qd])+np.array([-.0002,-.00002,0,0,0,0])
            
        t = np.linspace(0, years, years*days)
        m = np.zeros(years*days)
        sol = odeint(self.differentials, y0, t)
        self.trans = sol
        
        if graph:
            %matplotlib inline
            plt.plot(t, self.trans[:, 0], 'b', linewidth=2, label='consumption')
            plt.plot(t, self.trans[:, 1], 'red', linewidth=2,label='capital')
            plt.plot(t, self.trans[:, 4], 'g',linewidth=2, label='Qn')
            plt.plot(t, self.trans[:, 5], 'c',linewidth=2, label='Qd')
            plt.plot(t,self.Kinit, 'c--', linewidth=2, label='Initial K')
            plt.legend(loc='best')
            plt.xlabel('time')
            plt.title('Transition (Reverse)')
            plt.show()
        
        if ((K<Kinit) & (self.trans[-1,1] < self.Kinit[-1])) :
            print ('Increasing the transition years')
            years = years + 35
            t = np.linspace(0, years, years*days)
            m = np.zeros(years*days)
            sol = odeint(self.differentials, y0, t)
            self.trans = sol
            self.Kinit = np.ones(years*days)*Kinit

            
        elif ((K>Kinit) & (self.trans[-1,1] > self.Kinit[-1])):
            print ('Increasing the transition years')
            years = years + 35
            t = np.linspace(0, years, years*days)
            m = np.zeros(years*days)
            sol = odeint(self.differentials, y0, t)
            self.trans = sol 
            self.Kinit = np.ones(years*days)*Kinit

        elif (K==Kinit):
            return (self.C/init_c)*np.exp((-org_g_C+g_C)/self.rho)
        
    
        
        for i in range(years*days):
            if (K < Kinit):
                m[i] = -1 if self.trans[i,1] > self.Kinit[i] else 0
            else:
                m[i] = -1 if self.trans[i,1] < self.Kinit[i] else 0

        t0 = np.argmax(m<0)
        Ktrans     = self.trans[0:t0,1]
        Ctrans     = self.trans[0:t0,0]
        Qntrans    = self.trans[0:t0,4]
        Qdtrans    = self.trans[0:t0,5]

        Kseq = np.concatenate((self.Kinit[0:outyears*days],Ktrans[::-1],np.ones(5*outyears*days)*K))
        Cseq = np.concatenate((Cinit[0:outyears*days],Ctrans[::-1],np.ones(5*outyears*days)*C))
        
        Qn_earlier = [1/np.exp(taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)*i/days) for i in range(outyears*days)]
        Qd_earlier = [1/np.exp(taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)*i/days) for i in range(outyears*days)]
        
        Qntrans    = self.trans[0:t0,4]/self.trans[t0-1,4]*np.exp(taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)/days)
        Qdtrans    = self.trans[0:t0,5]/self.trans[t0-1,5]*np.exp(taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)/days)
        
        Qn_later  = [Qntrans[0]*np.exp(taun_late*np.log(self.lambda_n)*i/days) for i in range(5*outyears*days)]
        Qd_later  = [Qdtrans[0]*np.exp(taud_late*np.log(self.lambda_d)*i/days) for i in range(5*outyears*days)]
        
        self.Qnseq = np.concatenate((Qn_earlier[::-1],Qntrans[::-1],Qn_later))
        self.Qdseq = np.concatenate((Qd_earlier[::-1],Qdtrans[::-1],Qd_later))

        
        self.Cseq = Cseq
        self.Conseq = Cseq*self.Qnseq*self.Qdseq**(self.theta/(1-self.alpha))
        
        time = len(self.Conseq)
        
        self.Kseq = Kseq
        self.Capseq = Kseq*self.Qdseq**(1/(1-self.alpha))
        
        self.utility = [np.exp(-self.rho*(i-outyears*days)/days)*np.log(self.Conseq[i]) for i in range(time)]
        
        self.Conseqalt = np.zeros(time)
        self.Conseqalt[0:outyears*days] = self.Conseq[0:outyears*days]
        for i in range(outyears*days,time):
            self.Conseqalt[i]=self.Conseqalt[i-1]*np.exp((taun_init*np.log(self.lambda_n)+
                                                        taud_init*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha))/days)
        
        self.utilityalt=[np.exp(-self.rho*(i-outyears*days)/days)*np.log(self.Conseqalt[i]) for i in range(time)]
        

        self.Conseq_cg = np.zeros(time)
        self.Conseq_cg[0:outyears*days+1] = self.Conseq[0:outyears*days+1]
        

        

        for i in range(outyears*days+1,time):
            self.Conseq_cg[i]=self.Conseq_cg[i-1]*np.exp((taun_late*np.log(self.lambda_n)+
                                                        taud_late*np.log(self.lambda_d)*self.theta/(1-self.alpha))/days)

        self.con_growth = np.zeros(time)
        self.con_growth[0:outyears*days]=org_g_C
        self.con_growth[outyears*days+t0:]=g_C

        org_C    = self.Conseqalt[outyears*days]
        org_C_ss = self.Conseqalt[outyears*days+t0]
        C0       = self.Conseq[outyears*days]
        Css      = self.Conseq[outyears*days+t0]
 
        CE = (Css/org_C)*np.exp((-org_g_C+g_C)/self.rho)
        
        welfare_new = (np.exp(-self.rho*t0/days)*(np.log(Css)+g_C/self.rho)/self.rho
                       +trapz(self.utility[outyears*days:outyears*days+t0],dx=1/days))
        
        CE_alt = np.zeros(4)
        CE_alt[0] = np.exp(welfare_new*self.rho-org_g_C/self.rho-np.log(org_C))
        CE_alt[3] = (Css/org_C_ss)*np.exp((-org_g_C+g_C)/self.rho)
        for index,t in enumerate((10,20)):
            welfare_short = trapz(self.utility[outyears*days:(outyears+t)*days],dx=1/days)
            CE_alt[index+1]=np.exp((welfare_short-1/self.rho*np.log(org_C)
                             +np.exp(-self.rho*t)/self.rho*np.log(self.Conseqalt[(outyears+t)*days])
                            -(1-np.exp(-self.rho*t))*org_g_C/self.rho**2)*self.rho/(1-np.exp(-self.rho*t)))
        
        return CE_alt

    
    def costs(self,nsub,lower_bound,upper_bound, both=True, differ=False,inv_sub=False,plot_graph=False):
        self.correct = np.ones((nsub,nsub), dtype=bool)
        ns = np.linspace(lower_bound,upper_bound,nsub)
        ds = np.linspace(lower_bound,upper_bound,nsub)
        tax_cost = np.zeros(nsub*nsub)
        RD_cost  = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
        tax_cost.shape = (nsub,nsub)
        if inv_sub:
            self.s_x=1-1/self.lambda_d
            
        for index,n in enumerate(ns):
            self.s_in = n
            if both and not differ:
                self.s_en = n 
            elif both and differ:
                self.s_en = (n-self.gamma)/(1-self.gamma)
            else:
                self.s_en = 0
            
            for index2,d in enumerate(ds):
                self.s_id = d
                if both and not differ:
                    self.s_ed = d
                elif both and differ:
                    self.s_ed = (d-self.gamma)/(1-self.gamma)
                else:
                    self.s_ed = 0
                self.equilibrium()
                if ((self.z_n <= 0) | (self.z_d <= 0) | (self.tau_n >= 1) | (self.tau_d >= 1)):
                    self.correct[index,index2] = False
                tax_cost[index,index2]=((self.s_in*self.chi_in*self.b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_id*self.chi_id*self.b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_in*self.chi_en*self.psi_n*self.z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_id*self.chi_ed*self.psi_d*self.z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))*self.w#/(self.C+self.D*self.p_d)
                                        +self.s_x*self.D*self.p_d)/(self.C+self.D*self.p_d)

                RD_cost[index,index2]=(self.chi_in*self.b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.chi_id*self.b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.chi_en*self.psi_n*self.z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.chi_ed*self.psi_d*self.z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))*self.w/(self.C+self.D*self.p_d)
                                       
        
                                       
        if plot_graph:
            %matplotlib inline
            CS = plt.contourf(ds, ns, RD_cost, 15,
                  cmap=plt.cm.bone,
                  origin='upper')

            plt.title('R&D Expenditure / GDP',fontsize=14)
            plt.xlabel('Investment Sector Subsidy',fontsize=14)
            plt.ylabel('Consumption Sector Subsidy',fontsize=14)



            # Make a colorbar for the ContourSet returned by the contourf call.
            cbar = plt.colorbar(CS)
            cbar.ax.set_ylabel('R&D',fontsize=14)


            plt.savefig("RD_GDP.pdf",bbox_inches='tight')
        self.RD_cost = RD_cost                               
        
        return tax_cost
    
    def cost_spe_tax(self,subs):
        self.s_x,self.s_in,self.s_id,self.s_en,self.s_ed=subs
        self.equilibrium()
        
        tax_cost = np.zeros(4)
        tax_cost[0]=((self.s_in*self.chi_in*self.b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_id*self.chi_id*self.b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_en*self.chi_en*self.psi_n*self.z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_ed*self.chi_ed*self.psi_d*self.z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))*self.w)/(self.C+self.D*self.p_d)
                                        #+self.s_x*self.D*self.p_d)/(self.C+self.D*self.p_d)
        
        tax_cost[1]=((self.s_in*self.chi_in*self.b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_id*self.chi_id*self.b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_en*self.chi_en*self.psi_n*self.z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_ed*self.chi_ed*self.psi_d*self.z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))*self.w#/(self.C+self.D*self.p_d)
                                        +self.s_x*self.D*self.p_d)/(self.C+self.D*self.p_d)
        tax_cost[2]= ((self.s_in*self.chi_in*self.b_n**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_en*self.chi_en*self.psi_n*self.z_n**(1/(1-self.gamma)))*self.w)

        tax_cost[3]= ((self.s_id*self.chi_id*self.b_d**(1/(1-self.gamma))+
                                        self.s_ed*self.chi_ed*self.psi_d*self.z_d**(1/(1-self.gamma)))*self.w)


        
        return tax_cost
    
    def initiate(self):
        self.s_in = self.s_id = .2
        self.equilibrium()
        self.x0 = np.array([self.b_n, self.b_d, self.z_n, self.z_d, self.tau_n, self.tau_d,
                            self.Ln, self.Ld,self.D, self.C, self.C, self.K, self.RD,
                            self.w, self.r, self.p_d])
        return self.K
                                        
    def innovative_response(self,nsub,upper_bound,both=True,inv_sub=False):
        
        sss = np.linspace(0,upper_bound,nsub)
        taun_all = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
        taud_all = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
        self.correct = np.ones((nsub,nsub), dtype=bool)
        
        if inv_sub:
            self.s_x = 1-1/self.lambda_d
        else:
            self.s_x = 0
        
        self.s_in,self.s_id, self_en, self.s_ed = 0,0,0,0
        
        for index, sub_n in enumerate(sss):
            self.s_in = sub_n
            if both:
                self.s_en = sub_n
            
            for index2, sub_d in enumerate(sss):
                self.s_id = sub_d
                if both:
                    self.s_ed = sub_d
                
                self.equilibrium()
                taun_all[index,index2]=self.tau_n
                taud_all[index,index2]=self.tau_d
                
                if ((self.z_n <= 0) or (self.z_d <= 0) or (self.tau_n >= 1) or (self.tau_d >= 1)):
                    taun_all[index,index2]=0
                    taud_all[index,index2]=0
                    print ('Error', 'con sub',sub_n,'inv sub',sub_d)
                    print ('z_n',self.z_n,'z_d',self.z_d,'tau_n',self.tau_n,'tau_d',self.tau_d)
                    self.correct[index,index2]=False

        return taun_all, taud_all

Centrality of an industry and optimal innovation rates

In this excercise, I am at addressing reviewer 1's point about impact of position of a sector in I-O structure on optimal R&D.

After calibrating my model, I perform camparative statics on $\alpha$, elasticity of output w.r.t. capital. In the network literature, higher $\alpha$ represents higher level of centrality for the investment goods producing industry. I solve for competitive equilibrium and social planner allocations for different values of $\alpha$.

In [151]:
n_alp = 20
alpha_space = np.linspace(.24,.5,n_alp)
n_var = 15
n_var_ce = 13
def comparative_stats(cal):
    planner_cs= np.zeros((n_alp,n_var))
    competitive_cs= np.zeros((n_alp,n_var_ce))
    for index,alpha in enumerate(alpha_space):
        planner_cs[index,:] = cal.planner_cs(alpha)
        competitive_cs[index,:] = cal.competitive_cs(alpha)
    return planner_cs,competitive_cs
In [149]:
def plot_cs(planner,competitive,filename):
    plt.plot(alpha_space,planner[:,4],'r--',linewidth=2,label=r'Planner $\tau_n$')
    plt.plot(alpha_space,competitive[:,2],'r',linewidth=2,label=r'Competitive $\tau_n$')
    plt.plot(alpha_space,planner[:,5],'k--',linewidth=2,label=r'Planner $\tau_d$')
    plt.plot(alpha_space,competitive[:,3],'k',linewidth=2,label=r'Competitive $\tau_d$')
    plt.xlabel(r'$\alpha$')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.xlim(xmin=.24)
    plt.savefig(filename)
In [158]:
planner_cs_A,competitive_cs_A = comparative_stats(A)
plot_cs(planner_cs_A,competitive_cs_A,'comparative_A_tau_alpha.pdf')

In the above graph, I plot innovations rates in each sector for each $\alpha$. Dashed lines are steady state innovation rates in the planner problem, solid lines are steady state innovation rates in the competitive equilibrium.

In the planner problem, as $\alpha$ increase, innovation rate in investment goods producing industry increases, while innovation rate in the consumption sector decreases. This result is intuitive. As the centrality of an industry increases, social planner allocates more resources towards that sector.

In the competitive equilibrium, as $\alpha$ increases, innovation rates in both industries increase. However, increase in consumption sector innovation is mild.

In [159]:
def cal_cs_ratio(planner,competitive,filename):
    plt.plot(alpha_space,competitive[:,2]/planner[:,4],'r-.',linewidth=2,label=r'$\tau_n$')
    plt.plot(alpha_space,competitive[:,3]/planner[:,5],'k',linewidth=2,label=r'$\tau_d$')
    plt.xlabel(r'$\alpha$')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.xlim(xmin=.24)
    plt.savefig(filename)
In [162]:
cal_cs_ratio(planner_cs_A,competitive_cs_A,'comparative_A_tau_ratio_alpha.pdf')

Here, I plot competitve equilibrium innovaation rates relative to the social planner innovation rates. As $\alpha$ increases, investment good producing sector's innovation level in the competitive equilibrium diverges from the social planner level. On the other hand, consumption sector's innovation level in the competitive equilibrium converges to socially optimal level.

As the centrality of an industry increases, social planner allocates more innovative resources to that sector. However, since competitive equilibrium cannot internalize externalities, competitive equilibrium innovation rate does not increase as much in the investment sector. Similarly, as the centrality of investment sector increases, social planner allocates less resources to consumption sector. However, competitive equilibrium innovation rates are not affected much with the centrality of the other sector. Therefore, social planner innvoation rate in consumption sector approaches to CE innovation rates.

cost_points = 91
optimal_subsidy = np.zeros((2,cost_points))
cost_range = np.linspace(0.052,.2,cost_points)
costs = np.zeros(91)
welfares = np.zeros(91)
x_subs = np.zeros(91)
c_subs = np.zeros(91)
for i in range(cost_points):
    #cost = tax_cost[i,i]
    cost = cost_range[i]
    costs[i] = cost
    subsidies = [tax_cost <= cost]
    opt_welfare = np.max(welfare4B[subsidies])
    welfares[i]=opt_welfare
    opt_subsidy = np.argwhere(welfare4B==opt_welfare)
    optimal_subsidy[:,i]=(ns[opt_subsidy[0,0]],ds[opt_subsidy[0,1]])
    x_subs[i]=ds[opt_subsidy[0,1]]
    c_subs[i]=ns[opt_subsidy[0,0]]
    print ('Uniform Subsidy','{0:.2f}'.format(ns[i]) ,
           'Welfare','{0:.4f}'.format(welfare4B[i,i]), 'Cost', '{0:.3f}'.format(cost),
           'Inv Subsidy' , '{0:.2f}'.format(ds[opt_subsidy[0,1]]),'Con Subsidy' ,'{0:.2f}'.format(ns[opt_subsidy[0,0]]),
           'Optimal Welfare', '{0:.4f}'.format(opt_welfare))

In [30]:
cost_points = 91
optimal_subsidy = np.zeros((2,cost_points))
cost_range = np.linspace(0,.2,cost_points)
for i in range(cost_points):
    #cost = tax_cost[i,i]
    cost = cost_range[i]
    subsidies = [tax_cost_ <= cost]
    opt_welfare = np.max(welfare[subsidies])
    opt_subsidy = np.argwhere(welfare==opt_welfare)
    optimal_subsidy[:,i]=(ns[opt_subsidy[0,0]],ds[opt_subsidy[0,1]])
    print ('Cost', '{0:.3f}'.format(cost),
           'Inv Subsidy' , '{0:.2f}'.format(ds[opt_subsidy[0,1]]),'Con Subsidy' ,'{0:.2f}'.format(ns[opt_subsidy[0,0]]),
           'Optimal Welfare', '{0:.4f}'.format(opt_welfare))

years, days, outyears  = 72, 365, 5
nsub = 46
n_e = (.2-C.gamma)/(1-C.gamma)
init_subs=(1-1/C.lambda_d,.2,.2,n_e,n_e)
upper_bound = .9
ns = np.linspace(0,upper_bound,nsub)
ds = np.linspace(0,upper_bound,nsub)
welfareC    = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
welfareC_10 = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
welfareC_20 = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
welfareC_ss = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
for index,n in enumerate(ns):
    print ('Outer loop =', index)
    n_ent = (n-C.gamma)/(1-C.gamma)
    for index2,d in enumerate(ds):
        #print ('Inner loop =', index2)
        d_ent = (d-C.gamma)/(1-C.gamma)
        subs = (1-1/C.lambda_d,n,d,n_ent,d_ent)
        welfareC[index,index2],welfareC_10[index,index2],welfareC_20[index,index2],welfareC_ss[index,index2] = C.transition(init_subs,subs,years,days,outyears)

    #cost = tax_cost_[i,i]

    subsidies = [tax_cost_ <= cost]

           'Optimal Welfare', '{0:.4f}'.format(opt_welfare))

mar_cost_inc_n = 1/(1-A.gamma)*A.chi_in*A.b_n**(A.gamma/(1-A.gamma))
mar_cost_inc_d = 1/(1-A.gamma)*A.chi_id*A.b_d**(A.gamma/(1-A.gamma))
profit_n = A.Ln*(A.lambda_n-1)/(1-A.theta)*A.w-A.w*A.chi_in*A.b_n**(1/(1-A.gamma))
profit_d = A.Ld*(A.lambda_d-1)/(1-A.alpha)*A.w-A.w*A.chi_id*A.b_d**(1/(1-A.gamma))
discount_n = A.rho+A.tau_n-A.b_n
discount_d = A.rho+A.tau_d-A.b_d
print ('Marginal cost n ',mar_cost_inc_n)
print ('Marginal cost d ',mar_cost_inc_d)
print ('Net profit n', profit_n)
print ('Net profit d', profit_d)
print ('Wage Rate', A.w)
print ('Adjusted Discount Factor n', discount_n)
print ('Adjusted Discount Factor d', discount_d)

In [122]:
for i in range(nsub):
    cost = tax_cost[i,i]
    subsidies = [tax_cost <= cost]
    opt_welfare = np.max(welfare[subsidies])
    opt_subsidy = np.argwhere(welfare==opt_welfare)    
    print ('Uniform Subsidy','{0:.2f}'.format(ns[i]) ,
           'Welfare','{0:.4f}'.format(welfare[i,i]), 'Cost', '{0:.3f}'.format(cost),
           'Inv Subsidy' , '{0:.2f}'.format(ds[opt_subsidy[0,1]]),'Con Subsidy' ,'{0:.2f}'.format(ns[opt_subsidy[0,0]]),
           'Optimal Welfare', '{0:.4f}'.format(opt_welfare))

years, days, outyears  = 70, 365, 5
nsub = 46
upper_bound = .9
init_subs=(0,.2,.2,0,0)
ns = np.linspace(0,upper_bound,nsub)
ds = np.linspace(0,upper_bound,nsub)
welfare2 = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
for index,n in enumerate(ns):
    print ('Outer loop =', index)
    for index2,d in enumerate(ds):
        print ('Inner loop =', index2)
        subs = (0,n,d,n,d)
        welfare2[index,index2]=A.transition(init_subs,subs,years,days,outyears)[0]

g_C = np.zeros((nsub,nsub))
for n in range(nsub):
    for d in range(nsub):
        g_C[n,d]=taun_all[n,d]*np.log(A.lambda_n)+(A.theta)/(1-A.alpha)*taud_all[n,d]*np.log(A.lambda_d)

# How do innovation rates react to subsidies?
A.innovative_response()

z_n 0.292968564839 z_d 0.178028854128 b_n 0.0861773876013 b_d 0.0775596488411
In [17]:
# This exercise was conducted with initial way of calculating CE
# However, the numbers are still valid
# Calculate the innovation rates with uniform subsidy (.3) 
# and non-uniform subsidy (.05,.35) 

z_n_u,b_n_u = float(uniform[9]),float(uniform[13])#0.05646,0.10931
z_n_n,b_n_n = float(non_uniform[9]),float(non_uniform[13])#0.06507,0.08918

z_d_u,b_d_u = float(uniform[11]),float(uniform[15])#0.03517,0.09838
z_d_n,b_d_n = float(non_uniform[11]),float(non_uniform[15])#0.03293,0.10336 

l_rd_n_u = A.chi_en*A.psi_n*z_n_u+A.chi_in*b_n_u**(1/(1-A.gamma)) 
l_rd_n_n = A.chi_en*A.psi_n*z_n_n+A.chi_in*b_n_n**(1/(1-A.gamma)) 

l_rd_d_u = A.chi_ed*A.psi_d*z_d_u+A.chi_id*b_d_u**(1/(1-A.gamma)) 
l_rd_d_n = A.chi_ed*A.psi_d*z_d_n+A.chi_id*b_d_n**(1/(1-A.gamma)) 

print ('R&D Labor in Consumption with Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format(l_rd_n_u))
print ('R&D Labor in Consumption with Non-Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format(l_rd_n_n))
print ('R&D Labor in Investment with Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format(l_rd_d_u))
print ('R&D Labor in Investment with Non-Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format(l_rd_d_n))
print ('R&D Labor with Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format(l_rd_n_u+l_rd_d_u))
print ('R&D Labor with Non-Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format(l_rd_n_n+l_rd_d_n))
print ('Growth Rate with Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format((z_n_u+b_n_u)*np.log(A.lambda_n)+
                                                          (z_d_u+b_d_u)*np.log(A.lambda_d)*A.theta/(1-A.alpha)))
print ('Growth Rate with Non-Uniform Subsidy','{0:.5f}'.format((z_n_n+b_n_n)*np.log(A.lambda_n)+
                                                          (z_d_n+b_d_n)*np.log(A.lambda_d)*A.theta/(1-A.alpha)))

R&D Labor in Consumption with Uniform Subsidy 0.02833
R&D Labor in Consumption with Non-Uniform Subsidy 0.02424
R&D Labor in Investment with Uniform Subsidy 0.06688
R&D Labor in Investment with Non-Uniform Subsidy 0.07096
R&D Labor with Uniform Subsidy 0.09521
R&D Labor with Non-Uniform Subsidy 0.09520
Growth Rate with Uniform Subsidy 0.02067
Growth Rate with Non-Uniform Subsidy 0.02072
